.TH "ufshcd_wait_for_register" 9 "ufshcd_wait_for_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ufshcd_wait_for_register \- wait for register value to change
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ufshcd_wait_for_register
.BI "(struct ufs_hba *hba "  ","
.BI "u32 reg "  ","
.BI "u32 mask "  ","
.BI "u32 val "  ","
.BI "unsigned long interval_us "  ","
.BI "unsigned long timeout_ms "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hba" 12
per-adapter interface
.IP "reg" 12
mmio register offset
.IP "mask" 12
mask to apply to the read register value
.IP "val" 12
value to wait for
.IP "interval_us" 12
polling interval in microseconds
.IP "timeout_ms" 12
timeout in milliseconds
.SH "RETURN"
-ETIMEDOUT on error, zero on success.
